               <w>back-
               <lb/>side</w><!--2020-05-17 ebb: Note the use of the <w> element here to indicate a word is being broken across the line.  -->
               of an island in the pond, and <lb/>then concealed himself in the <lb/>bushes on the
               south side to await <lb/>them. The ice was melted out <lb/>3 or 4 rods from the
               shore, and <lb/>there was a smooth and warm sheet <lb/>of water, with a <zone
                  ulx="87" uly="522" lrx="787" lry="969" type="blockDeletion"><mod><handShift
                        medium="pencil"/><add place="left-margin-bottom">?</add><del rend="vstrike"
                        >muddy bottom <lb/>such as the ducks love within, and <lb/>he thought it
                        likely that some would <lb/>be along pretty soon. After he <lb/>had lain
                        still there about an <lb/>hour he <mod><del rend="hstrike"><handShift
                                 medium="ink2"/>suddenly</del></mod> heard a <mod><del
                              rend="vstrike"><handShift medium="ink2"/>s</del>low <lb/></mod>and
                        seemingly very distant sound, <lb/>and singularly grand and <w>im-
                           <lb/>pressive</w>, and unlike anything he <lb/>had ever heard before,
                        gradually <lb/>swelling and increasing as if it <lb/>would have a universal
                        and <lb/>memorable ending–a sudden <lb/>rush and roar, which seemed <lb/>to
